#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:21
msgid "Basic Components"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:23
msgid ""
"The basic components of a Xen-based virtualization environment are the "
"<emphasis>Xen hypervisor</emphasis>, the <emphasis>Dom0</emphasis>, any "
"number of other <emphasis>VM Guests</emphasis>, and the tools, commands, and "
"configuration files that let you manage virtualization. Collectively, the "
"physical computer running all these components is called a <emphasis>VM Host "
"Server</emphasis> because together these components form a platform for "
"hosting virtual machines."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: varlistentry/term
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:38
msgid "The Xen Hypervisor"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:40
msgid ""
"The Xen hypervisor, sometimes simply called a virtual machine monitor, is an "
"open source software program that coordinates the low-level interaction "
"between virtual machines and physical hardware."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: varlistentry/term
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:48
msgid "The Dom0"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:50
msgid ""
"The virtual machine host environment, also called <emphasis>Dom0</emphasis> "
"or controlling domain, is composed of several components, such as:"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:57
msgid ""
"<phrase role=\"productname\"><phrase os=\"osuse\">openSUSE Leap</"
"phrase><phrase os=\"sles\">SUSE Linux Enterprise Server</phrase><phrase os="
"\"sled\">SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop</phrase></phrase> provides a "
"graphical and a command line environment to manage the virtual machine host "
"components and its virtual machines."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: note/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:62
msgid ""
"The term <quote>Dom0</quote> refers to a special domain that provides the "
"management environment. This may be run either in graphical or in command "
"line mode."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:70
msgid ""
"The xl tool stack based on the xenlight library (libxl). Use it to manage "
"Xen guest domains."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:76
msgid ""
"QEMU—an open source software that emulates a full computer system, including "
"a processor and various peripherals. It provides the ability to host "
"operating systems in both full virtualization or paravirtualization mode."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: varlistentry/term
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:87
msgid "Xen-Based Virtual Machines"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:89
msgid ""
"A Xen-based virtual machine, also called a <replaceable>VM Guest</"
"replaceable> or <replaceable>DomU</replaceable>, consists of the following "
"components:"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:96
msgid ""
"At least one virtual disk that contains a bootable operating system. The "
"virtual disk can be based on a file, partition, volume, or other type of "
"block device."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/xen_virtualization_basics.xml:103
msgid ""
"A configuration file for each guest domain. It is a text file following the "
"syntax described in the manual page <command>man 5 xl.conf</command>."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
